Label: Multidrug-resistant bacteria (organism)
Definition: Multi Drug Resistance (MDR) is defined as non-susceptibility to at least one agent in three or more epidemiologically significant antimicrobial categories. Non-susceptibility refers to either a resistant, intermediate or non-susceptible result obtained from in vitro antimicrobial susceptibility testing. (DOI: 10.1111/j.1469-0691.2011.03570.x)
